// Every module in this repository, wired together for local development.
//
// The backend modules (s3, gcs, azure) each `require` a published version of
// the root module. Without this workspace they would compile against that
// published version even here, so a breaking change to the root would pass CI
// while silently breaking every backend. The workspace overrides that
// requirement with the working tree.
//
// No module in this repo carries a `replace` directive; this file is the only
// place local resolution is configured. It is committed so CI uses it too, and
// it is ignored entirely when someone depends on any of these modules.
//
// Releasing bumps each backend's `require` to the new root tag (see
// CONTRIBUTING.md). That stays on main safely, precisely because the workspace
// still points local builds at the working tree.
//
// To reproduce a consumer's build instead, set GOWORK=off.

go 1.26

use (
	.
	./azure
	./gcs
	./s3
)
